Package: treedataverse
Title: Easily Install and Load the 'treedataverse'
Version: 0.0.1
Authors@R: c(
            person("Guangchuang", "Yu",     email = "guangchuangyu@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre", "cph"), comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-6485-8781"))
  )
Description: The 'treedataverse' is set of packages (mainly 'tidytree', 'treeio', 'ggtree', and 'ggtreeExtra')
             that work for processing and visualizing trees with associated data. This package is designed to
             make it easy to install and load multiple 'treedataverse' packages in a single step. 
Depends: 
    R (>= 3.1)
Imports: 
    ape,
    cli (>= 1.0.0),
    crayon (>= 1.3.4),
    dplyr (>= 0.7.4),
    purrr (>= 0.2.4),
    magrittr,
    rstudioapi (>= 0.7),
    tidytree,
    tibble (>= 1.4.2),
    treeio,
    ggplot2,
    ggtree,
    ggtreeExtra
Encoding: UTF-8
